# Doxygen Documentation Standards

## Requirement

All public functions SHALL be documented using Doxygen comment style.

All function documentation SHALL include:
- A brief description of the function's purpose
- Documentation for each parameter using `@param`
- Documentation for the return value using `@return`
- Any relevant notes or warnings using `@note` or `@warning`

All source files SHALL include file-level documentation with:
- A brief description of the file's purpose
- Author information (if applicable)
- Copyright information (if applicable)

Doxygen comments SHALL use the `/** */` style for block comments.

Inline documentation SHALL be provided for complex algorithms or non-obvious code sections.
